<HEADLINE>
TAIPEI MAIN STATION TO HOLD EVACUATION EXERCISE WITH 3 REHEARSALS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 2 (CNA) 05/02/07  18:06:48 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
The Taipei city government will hold an evacuation exercise May 9
in the Taipei Main Station to enhance the ability  of government
and private units when responding  to emergencies.
</P>
<P>
The Taipei City Police Bureau, chief planner of the exercise,
indicated Thursday that prior to the formal exercise, scheduled
to begin at 8:30 a.m. May 9, three rehearsals will be held May 3,
May 7 and May 8 between 9:30 a.m. and noon.
</P>
<P>
Certain areas used for the three different rail services provided
by the Taiwan Railway Administration, the Taipei Rapid Transit
System and the Taiwan High Speed Rail will be closed, but train
operations will not be affected, according to the police.
</P>
<P>
Some of the roads around the station, including Peiping East Road
and Peiping West Road, will be blocked off, while traffic
controls will be enforced on other roads during the evacuation
and the rehearsals.
</P>
<P>
Police officers said that only city buses, official vehicles and
satellite news trucks will be allowed into the area, while
drivers of other vehicles are advised to made detours or follow
the instructions of traffic police at roadblocks.
</P>
